Onyebuchi Ezigbo in Abuja The National Working Committee (NWC) of the All Progressives Congress (APC) has set up a 5-man committee to review the numerous petitions on anti-party activities of some members in states. In a statement issued Monday night by its National Publicity Secretary, the party said that it had received several petitions alleging various forms of anti-party activities by some members, including those working against the party or our candidates in the just concluded elections. The partyâ€™s Deputy National Chairman (South), Otunba Niyi Adebayo, is Chairman of the Committee. Other members are National Vice Chairman (South-west), Mr. Bankole Oluwajana; National Legal Adviser, Babatunde Ogala; National Treasurer, Adamu Fanda, and National Disabled Leader, Misbau Lawal Didi. The statement said that the Committee had one week to submit its report.